---
import Prose from "@components/Prose.astro";
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  pageTitle="Now | Hyun Don Moon"
  pageDescription="What I'm up to right now"
>
  <Prose>
    <h1>Now</h1>

    <p>
      This page is inspired by Derek Sivers' <a
        href="https://nownownow.com/about"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer">/now pages</a
      > movement. It's a simple concept: a page that tells you what someone is focused
      on at this point in their life.
    </p>

    <section>
      <h3>September, 2025</h3>

      <ul>
        <li>
          <p>
            <strong>Work</strong>: Enjoyed a company outing to see the new F1
            movie, followed by a team barbecue.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            <strong>Learning</strong>: I started learning Python with the goal
            of getting into AI development and have been watching ThePrimeagen's videos for coding inspiration.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            <strong>Reading</strong>: I dropped <em>Deep Work</em> and started
            reading <em>Tiny Experiments</em> by Anne-Laure Le Cunff, which I'm
            already enjoying.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            <strong>Gaming</strong>: I bought <em>Divinity: Original Sin 2</em> for the
            Switch and have been playing a lot of FIFA Online with friends.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            <strong>Other</strong>: Assembled a new Linneback chair from Ikea, took a
            day off to visit my parents, and caught up with friends over dinner
            and drinks.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p style="margin-top:2em; font-size:0.9em; color: #666;">
        This page was updated automatically using n8n & Google Gemini.
      </p>
    </section>
  </Prose>
</BaseLayout>